The paper proposes new reward mechanisms for crowdsourcing evaluation tasks, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the ability of the mechanisms to account for heterogeneity in agents' abilities, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the issue of eliciting truthful responses from agents, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of output agreement mechanisms, which is a topic in cybersecurity (cs.CY).
